did.unittitle: Rockefeller University collection of The Medical Letter publication

bioghist.head: Biographical/Historical note
bioghist.p: Martin A. Rizack is an editor for THE MEDICAL LETTER. THE MEDICAL LETTER on Drugs and Therapeutics is an independent, non-profit publication providing unbiased critical evaluation of Drugs in terms of their effectiveness, adverse effects and possible alternative medications.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: Published printed material supplied by non-profit publication.

Material consists of files used in preparing articles for THE MEDICAL LETTER for the years 1959 to 1977; each file consisting of drafts of the article, letters from consultants and manufacturers; and copies of published articles from the medical and scientific literature which were used in preparing the articles. Some in folders and some in envelopes.
Additional materials are available through 1985 (Boxes 398-688) which have received standard processing, and are described in an available PDF.

phystech.head: Physical Characteristics and Technical Requirements
phystech.p: Materials requiring specialized equipment for access (film, audio, video, slides) may be closed to research dependent on availability of the applicable equipment
Brittle or damaged items, or materials otherwise in need of preservation care, may be closed to researchers at the discretion of the RAC Head of Archival Services/Head of Reference.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition note
acqinfo.p: Initial Date received/inventoried : July 29, 1982. Rockefeller Archive Center receives additions to the collection on an annual basis.

processinfo.head: Processing Information note
processinfo.p: Initial processeing by Gladys Lewis August 1982. Processing of additions to the collection are ongoing, and records are now available through 1985 (Boxes 398-688).

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access note
accessrestrict.p: Records are open for scholarly research twenty-five years after their creation.
Use agreement is required prior to providing scholarly access. See RAC Head of Reference for assistance.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Information regarding the Rockefeller Archive Center's preferred elements and forms of citation can be found at http://www.rockarch.org/research/citations.php
